ays of appreciating artistic skill and attending to their own processes of perception, thereby forging a court culture that delighted in the exercise of fine aesthetic judgment. Challenging modern assumptions about the nature of artistic production and reception, A Feast for the Eyes yields fresh insight into the long history of multimedia work and the complex relationships between spectacle and spectators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDinners and dining in art. 0aDinners and diningzEuropexHistoryy14th century. 0aDinners and diningzEuropexHistoryy15th century. 0aEntremésxHistoryy14th century. 0aEntremésxHistoryy15th century. 0aFasts and feasts in art. 0aFasts and feastszEuropexHistoryy14th century. 0aFasts and feastszEuropexHistoryy15th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022624220040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226242347423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226242347/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles